  "_comment": "Curated people-search broker seed for the Privacy Center opt-out engine (issue #2144, epic #2138). Shipped in data.reference/ (data/ is gitignored); loaded/upserted into Postgres privacy_brokers on first use — NO network at boot. Curated rows carry source=curated, confidence=field_verified|documented and are NEVER overwritten by the auto refresh (BADBOOL / CA registry). `urls.search` is a template with {firstName} {lastName} {state} {city} tokens; the scan engine fills them from vault scan vectors and never discloses anything outside disclosure_fields ∩ the fixed allowlist {full_name,email,phone,city,state,dob,listing_url}. cluster_parent groups sibling brands under one suppression (PeopleConnect covers Intelius/TruthFinder/InstantCheckmate/US Search); prefer_suppression on the parent because a per-brand deletion wipes the cluster suppression.",
